definitions: (of a letter or parcel) stamped with an official mark to indicate that postage has been paid or does not need to be paid

examples.text: undelivered franked mail without a return address will be disposed of

definitions: denoting dividends and other payments carrying a tax credit that can be offset against advance corporation tax by the company that receives them

examples.text: the nation's fourth largest lender also increased its fully franked interim dividend by 10 cents
